  "prompt": "What's the one song that can fix any bad mood?",
  "response": "While musical preferences are highly personal and can vary widely from person to person, there are certain songs that are often cited as universal mood-boosters due to their upbeat tempo, positive lyrics, or nostalgic value. One such song that frequently appears on such lists is **\"Don\u2019t Stop Me Now\" by Queen**. Its energetic rhythm, Freddie Mercury\u2019s dynamic vocals, and the empowering lyrics (\"I\u2019m a shooting star leaping through the sky\") make it a go-to anthem for lifting spirits.\n\nOther contenders include:\n\n- **\"Uptown Funk\" by Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars** (for its infectious groove)\n- **\"Happy\" by Pharrell Williams** (for its joyful vibe)\n- **\"Dancing Queen\" by ABBA** (for its timeless feel-good energy)\n\nUltimately, the \"one song\" that can fix *your* bad mood might be one that holds personal meaning or brings back happy memories. What\u2019s your go-to happy song? \ud83c\udfb5",
